OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772572328
OL,3,CHow an octopus surge is 'destroying'
OL,4,Cthe inshore fishing industry in
OL,5,CSalcombe
OL,7,FA fisherman from South Devon has said
OL,8,Fhe is considering leaving the industry
OL,9,Fbecause of an octopus boom which is
OL,10,F"destroying" crab and shellfish stocks.
OL,12,FPaul Dornon, who operates out of
OL,13,FSalcombe Harbour, said that last year
OL,14,Fsome inshore fishermen across
OL,15,FPlymouth, Salcombe and Dartmouth,
OL,16,Freported losing up to 90% of their
OL,17,Fcatch. Paul says he lost around 80%.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772572328
OL,3,CHow an octopus surge is 'destroying'
OL,4,Cthe inshore fishing industry in
OL,5,CSalcombe
OL,7,FThe influx of octopus meant that vast
OL,8,Fquantities of shellfish were eaten by
OL,9,Fthe animals, and piles of empty shells
OL,10,Fwere left behind in fishermen's pots.
OL,12,FIt was costing Paul more money to
OL,13,Flaunch his boat, than the cash he was
OL,14,Fmaking catching shellfish.
OL,16,F"It's been soul-destroying", Paul told
OL,17,FITV News.
OL,19,F"If we have another year like last
OL,20,Fyear, you've got to think, what's the
OL,21,Fpoint on doing this?
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772572328
OL,3,CHow an octopus surge is 'destroying'
OL,4,Cthe inshore fishing industry in
OL,5,CSalcombe
OL,7,F"It's 14-hour days, six or seven days
OL,8,Fa week. It should be about the reward,
OL,9,Fbut if there isn't the reward come
OL,10,Fthis time next year...I don't want to
OL,11,Fpack up, but if the money is not
OL,12,Fthere. We may have to."
OL,14,FNot all fishermen have been adversely
OL,15,Fimpacted by the surge. Some have made
OL,16,Fmoney by diversifying and catching
OL,17,Flarge quantities of octopus.
OL,19,FHowever, this is down to 'luck',
OL,20,Faccording to local conservation
OL,21,Fexperts.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772572328
OL,3,CHow an octopus surge is 'destroying'
OL,4,Cthe inshore fishing industry in
OL,5,CSalcombe
OL,7,FSarah Clark, Deputy Chief Officer for
OL,8,FDevon and Severn Inshore Fisheries and
OL,9,FConservation Authority, said: "In
OL,10,FSouth Devon, fishermen don't move
OL,11,Ftheir pots around.
OL,13,F"There is a gentlemen's agreement that
OL,14,Feach of the fishermen work in their
OL,15,Fset areas.
OL,17,F"The octopus haven't moved across the
OL,18,Farea equally, perhaps due to different
OL,19,Fhabitats under the water. Some areas
OL,20,Fare sandier or rockier than others.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772572328
OL,3,CHow an octopus surge is 'destroying'
OL,4,Cthe inshore fishing industry in
OL,5,CSalcombe
OL,7,F"Because of this, it's been about
OL,8,Fluck. Some are able to catch the
OL,9,Foctopus and some aren't," Sarah said.
OL,11,FThe Marine Management Organisation
OL,12,F(MMO), which regulates marine affairs
OL,13,Fon behalf of the Department for
OL,14,FEnvironment, Food and Rural Affairs
OL,15,F(DEFRA), held a meeting with the South
OL,16,FDevon inshore fishing community.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772572328
OL,3,CHow an octopus surge is 'destroying'
OL,4,Cthe inshore fishing industry in
OL,5,CSalcombe
OL,7,FFishermen asked for direct support and
OL,8,Femergency funding, particularly for
OL,9,Fthe fishermen, like Paul Dornom, who
OL,10,Fhave barely been able to make a living
OL,11,Fwage since spring last year.
OL,13,FPaul says, diversification could be an
OL,14,Foption, but it is expensive to buy new
OL,15,Fequipment and the correct licence.
OL,17,FAn MMO spokesperson said: "We are
OL,18,Factively monitoring landings data for
OL,19,Foctopus and key stocks, including crab
OL,20,Fand lobster.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772572328
OL,3,CHow an octopus surge is 'destroying'
OL,4,Cthe inshore fishing industry in
OL,5,CSalcombe
OL,7,F"We are working closely with
OL,8,Fscientists, regulators and industry
OL,9,Fstakeholders to understand the full
OL,10,Fscale of the situation.
OL,12,F"We are also exploring options for
OL,13,Ffinancial support, including through
OL,14,Fthe Fishing and Coastal Growth Fund."
OL,16,FA research study has been undertaken
OL,17,Fby a coalition of scientists, looking
OL,18,Finto why the octopus surge occurred in
OL,19,F2025 - it was the fourth boom in 150
OL,20,Fyears.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772572328
OL,3,CHow an octopus surge is 'destroying'
OL,4,Cthe inshore fishing industry in
OL,5,CSalcombe
OL,7,FThe study was funded by Plymouth City
OL,8,FCouncil, Devon County Council and
OL,9,FDEFRA.
OL,11,FDr Bryce Stewart, Senior Research
OL,12,FFellow at the Marine Biological
OL,13,FAssociation in Plymouth, said: "We
OL,14,Fthink it's down to a combination of
OL,15,Fenvironmental conditions, particularly
OL,16,Fwarmer than average water temperatures.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772572328
OL,3,CHow an octopus surge is 'destroying'
OL,4,Cthe inshore fishing industry in
OL,5,CSalcombe
OL,7,F"We've also had long spells of
OL,8,Feasterly winds, and we think that when
OL,9,Fthe octopus hatch out of their eggs,
OL,10,Fthey're being brought here by the
OL,11,Focean current from places like
OL,12,FNorthern France and the Channel
OL,13,FIslands.
OL,15,F"The likelihood is that this bloom
OL,16,Fwill continue. We have these warmer
OL,17,Fsea temperatures now and we are not
OL,18,Fgetting the colder winters that used
OL,19,Fto kill the octopus off.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772572328
OL,3,CHow an octopus surge is 'destroying'
OL,4,Cthe inshore fishing industry in
OL,5,CSalcombe
OL,7,F"Plus they are also breeding in UK
OL,8,Fwaters now. So they are probably here
OL,9,Fto stay."
OL,11,FThe South Devon inshore fishing
OL,12,Fcommunity are waiting to hear further
OL,13,Ffrom the MMO and the details of what,
OL,14,Fif any, support will be provided
OL,15,Fthrough the Fishing and Coastal Growth
OL,16,FFund.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
